The Meydan One Mall, next-generation retail & lifestyle, and the biggest mall in Dubai that is considered to be an epic addition to the Dubai retail scene is projected to open this year. Initially, the mall was set to be opened in 2020, however, mainly due to the worldwide pandemic and some delays here and there, the date was pushed towards the end of 2022. Located between Meydan and Al Khail Road, the Meydan One Mall is developed by Meydan Group as part of the first phase of the Meydan One mixed-use development project that includes several other components such as the Dubai One Tower, residential apartments, a civic plaza, a water park, and the world’s highest sky-view restaurant. Upon completion, the Meydan One Mall is will become one of the most visited leisure, entertainment, and shopping destination, and one of the biggest malls in Dubai. The Meydan One Mall will have a total of 620 retail shops, including two major department stores and a hypermarket spread over an area of 131,150ft².” It will also be home to the biggest indoor ski slope in Dubai. The ski slope will be 1 kilometer long, which makes it the longest indoor downhill ski slope, accompanied by a 12,000 sqm Winter Village. This will most definitely result in the Meydan One Mall giving Ski Dubai tough competition in the long-term as one of the best indoor ski slopes in the world. Read Also Mohammed Bin Rashid (MBR) City Project Updates, Dubai It will also have a dancing water fountain spread over 25,000 sqm according to the malls’ website. There is reportedly a huge probability of the fountain qualifying for the world’s biggest of its kind.